 aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5757789\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5757789\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 19, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zii1704964501123.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zii1704964501123.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zii1704964501123.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"rlg1665702612211\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                 \n Define the Component Structure\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">For services and server pages, use the Define Structure worksheet to add and organize entities and fields in the component structure.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"rlg1665702612211__context_w938ab1b5b1_w939ab1b5_w940ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"rlg1665702612211__topic_d11951e1_d11952e1_d11953e1\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"rlg1665702612211__p_d11954e1_d11955e1_d11956e1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span>  For form and report components, use\n               the Define Frames worksheet to graphically define both the component structure and\n               the layout. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cvl1690356504825.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cvl1690356504825.html\" title=\"Use the Define Frames worksheet to graphically define both the component data structure and the layout of the component.\">Define the Structure and Layout of Forms and Reports</a>. </div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step\" id=\"rlg1665702612211__li_d5516e1_d5517e1_d5518e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Open the component and go to the Define Structure worksheet. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xok1665702686298.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xok1665702686298.html\" title=\"Each main development object is opened in its own editor.\">Open a Main Development Object for Editing</a>.\n                  </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"rlg1665702612211__li_d5519e1_d5520e1_d5521e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Add entities and fields.\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"rlg1665702612211__li_d5522e1_d5523e1_d5524e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"rlg1665702612211__p_d11957e1_d11958e1_d11959e1\">In the Resource Browser, browse and select\n                     an entity template or a modeled entity, and drag and drop it onto the component\n                     object in the structure. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"flj1690357335479.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/flj1690357335479.html\" title=\"You can select templates, modeled objects, and code snippets in the Resource Browser and add them to current object. You can drag and drop objects, or use the context menu.\">Add Objects from the Resource Browser</a>. </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"rlg1665702612211__li_d5525e1_d5526e1_d5527e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"rlg1665702612211__p_d11960e1_d11961e1_d11962e1\">For each entity, select the fields you want to include in the component, and drag and drop them onto the entity in the Structure Editor.\n You can select multiple fields using Windows conventions of <span class=\"ph keypress\">Ctrl</span>Click or <span class=\"ph keypress\">Shift</span>Click.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rlg1665702612211__p_d11963e1_d11964e1_d11965e1\">The fields listed in the Templates tab represent non-database fields with a specific widget type and data type. They can be added to any entity in the component and renamed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rlg1665702612211__p_d11966e1_d11967e1_d11968e1\">Fields belonging to modeled entities can only be added to their parent entity and inherit their definitions from the model.</p>\n</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"rlg1665702612211__li_d5528e1_d5529e1_d5530e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"rlg1665702612211__p_d11969e1_d11970e1_d11971e1\">Modify the properties of component entities\n                     and fields, if required. For modeled fields, you can usually just use the\n                     inherited values, but you can always change properties to fit the specific\n                     component, thereby overriding inheritance and creating a <dfn class=\"term\">component\n                        variation</dfn>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"rlg1665702612211__note_w941ab1b5b3b3b3b5b3b1_w942ab1b5b3b3b3b5b3_w943ab1b5b3b3b3b5_w944ab1b5b3b3b3_w945ab1b5b3b3_w946ab1b5b3_w947ab1b5_w948ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> To revert a component variation to the model default, clear the\n                        property.</div>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"rlg1665702612211__li_d5531e1_d5532e1_d5533e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Change entity and field order. To change the order of fields and entities, you need to cut and paste them.\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"rlg1665702612211__li_d5534e1_d5535e1_d5536e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the Structure Editor, select the entity or field to move, right-click and choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Cut</span>.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"rlg1665702612211__li_d5537e1_d5538e1_d5539e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"rlg1665702612211__p_d11972e1_d11973e1_d11974e1\">Select an object where you want to paste the entity or field, right-click, and choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Paste After</span> or <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Paste Before</span>.\n When entities are moved, their child fields are also moved.</span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/djm1704694970422.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Component Data Structure</a><p>Every component has a data structure that defines its component entities and fields, and the path required to access the data. The data structure affects the validation rules for data I/O, such as enforcing referential integrity constraints.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5757789\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5757789\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define the Component Structure Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 19, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define the Component Structure For services and server pages, use the Define Structure worksheet to add and organize entities and fields in the component structure. Note: For form and report components, use the Define Frames worksheet to graphically define both the component structure and the layout. For more information, see Define the Structure and Layout of Forms and Reports . Open the component and go to the Define Structure worksheet. For more information, see Open a Main Development Object for Editing . Add entities and fields. In the Resource Browser, browse and select an entity template or a modeled entity, and drag and drop it onto the component object in the structure. For more information, see Add Objects from the Resource Browser . For each entity, select the fields you want to include in the component, and drag and drop them onto the entity in the Structure Editor. You can select multiple fields using Windows conventions of Ctrl Click or Shift Click. The fields listed in the Templates tab represent non-database fields with a specific widget type and data type. They can be added to any entity in the component and renamed. Fields belonging to modeled entities can only be added to their parent entity and inherit their definitions from the model. Modify the properties of component entities and fields, if required. For modeled fields, you can usually just use the inherited values, but you can always change properties to fit the specific component, thereby overriding inheritance and creating a component variation . Tip: To revert a component variation to the model default, clear the property. Change entity and field order. To change the order of fields and entities, you need to cut and paste them. In the Structure Editor, select the entity or field to move, right-click and choose Cut . Select an object where you want to paste the entity or field, right-click, and choose Paste After or Paste Before . When entities are moved, their child fields are also moved. Related Links Component Data Structure Every component has a data structure that defines its component entities and fields, and the path required to access the data. The data structure affects the validation rules for data I/O, such as enforcing referential integrity constraints. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}